DESCRIPTION.P:
To return to the visible mode, it will be necessary to set a Visibility
    property back to "on" value using the drawnow
    function. As a mirror, you can use:

MAN.EXAMPLE:
Example 1 // one axes / one figure
set("figure_style","new") // select entity based graphics
drawlater(); 
xfarc(.25,.55,.1,.15,0,64*360);
xfarc(.55,.55,.1,.15,0,64*360);
xfrect(.3,.8,.3,.2); 
xfrect(.2,.7,.5,.2);  
xfrect(.32,.78,.1,.1);
xfrect(.44,.78,.14,.1);
xfrect(-.2,.4,1.5,.8);
xstring(0.33,.9,"A Scilab Car");    
a=get("current_axes");
a.children(1).font_size=4;
a.children(1).font_style=4;  
a.children(1).foreground=5;
a.children(3).foreground=8;
a.children(4).foreground=8; 
a.children(5).foreground=17;
a.children(6).foreground=17; 
a.children(7).foreground=25;
a.children(8).foreground=25;
xclick();drawnow();

Example 2 // two axes / one figure

subplot(212)
a=gca();
drawlater(a) // what will be present in this axes will be displayed later
plot2d // draw these axes and children later...

subplot(211) // Warning: we change the axes
plot2d1 // default drawing mode

drawnow(a) // ...now!
